4 Using arrange() and mutate() with group_by()

  1. Lets explore how arrange() works with group_by() using a toy dataset.
toy <- tibble(
  x = c(4, 2, 2, 3, 3, 1, 3, 4, 5),
  group = c("c", "b", "a", "c", "b", "a", "a", "b", "c")
)

Suppose we would like to sort x in an increasing order within each group like this

## # A tibble: 9  2
## # Groups:   group [3]
##       x group
##   <dbl> <chr>
## 1     1 a    
## 2     2 a    
## 3     3 a    
## 4     2 b    
## 5     3 b    
## 6     4 b    
## 7     3 c    
## 8     4 c    
## 9     5 c

Does the following code work?

toy %>%
  group_by(group) %>%
  arrange(x)

Make some changes to sort within each group. (Hint: there are two ways. 1. sort with multiple variables; 2. check the .by_group argument of arrange() function)
